# Vendored third-party dependencies under libs/.
# These are git subtrees of upstream projects. Marking them as
# linguist-vendored tells GitHub:
#   1. exclude them from the repo's language statistics
#   2. collapse their files by default in PR diff views (reviewers
#      can click "Load diff" to expand).
# First-party files under libs/ (fake-dlclose, patches, CMakeLists.txt)
# are deliberately not marked so they remain reviewable.

libs/spdlog/**     linguist-vendored
libs/eigen/**      linguist-vendored
libs/pmt/**        linguist-vendored
libs/highway/**    linguist-vendored
libs/googletest/** linguist-vendored
libs/yaml-cpp/**   linguist-vendored
libs/antlr4/**     linguist-vendored
libs/ALL/**        linguist-vendored
libs/harmony/**    linguist-vendored